Download eclipse and Install pydev

In Eclipse , menu, “Help –> Install New Software..” and click on Add
Put URL http://pydev.org/updates and click Ok. Select “PyDev” option and click on Next restart Eclipse once completed.

Now Install python 2.7 and Google App Engine SDK for Python

Below steps to show you how to create a GAE project via Pydev plugin

Eclipse menu, File -> New -> project type pydev then choose “PyDev Google App Engine Project“.

Type project name(Hello_World), if the interpreter is not configure yet you can do it now. And select this option – “Add Project directory to the PYTHONPATH“. click Next
Click “Browse” button and point it to the Google App Engine installed directory
Name your application id in GAE, type anything, you can change it later. And choose “Hello Webapp World” template to generate the sample files. click Finish
(hello-adi)(Hello Web App World)
Done, 2 files are generated, app.yaml(configuration file) and helloworld.py(python file)
To run it locally, right click on the helloworld.py, choose “Run As” –> “Run Configuration”, create a new “PyDev Google App Run“. In Main tab -> Main module, manually type the directory path of “dev_appserver.py“. “Browse” button is not able to help you, type manually
In Arguments tab -> Program arguments, put “${project_loc}/src“.

Click on Apply.

Run it. By default, it will deploy to http://localhost:8080.

Done. Copy url and paste into the browser.
Deploy to Google App Engine
Register an account on Google App Engine and create application ID.
Open your “app.yaml” file. Replace your application field with your application ID.
application: sample-app
version: 1
runtime: python27
# threadsafe is required but can be either true or 
# false. For some package, it should be true e.g. Flask
threadsafe: true
api_version: 1

handlers:
- url: /.*
  script: helloworld.app
Create another new “PyDev Google App Run”, In Main tab -> Main module, manually type the directory path of “appcfg.py“.
In Arguments tab -> Program arguments, put “update ${project_loc}/src“.
During deployment process you need to have your GAE email and password for authentication. it'll redirect automatic for authentication.

Run your app with URL - https://yourappid.appspot.com
